records.addlTxt:
John Vaughn, sworn to interpret.
Amended Information filed amending Count 1 to misdemeanor battery contrary to sec. 940.19(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes and Count 2 to disorderly conduct contrary to sec. 947.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.
Count 1 - Guilty plea to amended charge.  Convicted.
Count 2 - Guilty plea to amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentences are withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years concurrent.  Conditions of probation:
1) COMPAS assessment;
2) No contact with the victim;
3) Maintain full-time employment;
4) Provide a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
5) One hundred twenty (120) days Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, commencing 06-22-16 by 8:00 a.m.;
6) Pay costs of the action (apply bail); and
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
